3 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Requirement of certification of compliance -- penalties for
4 noncompliance -- powers of attorney general. (1) (a) Each medical facility and research institution covered
5 under [sections 1 through 7 6] shall provide legal documentation from an attorney to the attorney general by
6 [December 31 following the effective date of this act], and annually thereafter, certifying that the facility or
7 institution is in compliance with [sections 4 AND 5 and 6].
8 (b) Failure to provide documentation by the deadline constitutes perjury.
9 (2) (a) A medical facility or research institution that violates the provisions of [section 5 4] shall be
10 fined $10,000 for each violation, enforceable from the first day of the first full fiscal year after [the effective date
11 of this act].
12 (b) For the purposes of this subsection (2), "violation" means each unique instance of an
13 individual's genome having undergone genetic sequencing or analysis using prohibited genetic sequencers or
14 prohibited operational and research software used for genetic sequencers or genetic sequencing.
15 (3) An entity that knowingly violates the provisions of [section 6 5] by storing genetic sequencing
16 data outside of the United States shall be fined $10,000 for each violation, enforceable beginning the first day of
17 the first full fiscal year after [the effective date of this act].
18 (4) (a) A person may notify the attorney general of a violation or a potential violation of [sections 1
19 through 7 6]. If that person is an employee of the entity accused of a violation, the person must be afforded all
20 the protections of a whistleblower pursuant to 30-10-1111.
21 (b) If a person is a patient or research subject of an entity found guilty of a violation of [section 5 4]
22 or [section 6 5] and that person's genetic information was used in the violation, that person is entitled to recover
23 damages of not less than $5,000 for each unique use of the person's genomic information.
24 (5) The attorney general has the authority to investigate allegations of violations of [sections 1
25 through 7 6].
